      "text": "When Lyndon Johnson signed the Civil Rights Act of 1964, few could have imagined only years earlier that such a bill was possible. With the stroke of a pen, the end of legal segregation was written into law, moving us closer to the founding promise of life, liberty, and the https://t.co/ruw4QIfgbt",
